This literal cellar is cozy and tucked away in the heart of Downtown Frederick. A lively mixed crowd. Its a great place to get lost alone or with a buddy..or a few friends. The vibe is so upbeat and jazzy. Service is prompt and friendly. I had the pleasure of visiting during Frederick Resturant Week. The menu was quite inviting and EVERYTHING sounded delish. I had the crab balls appetizer...they were fantastic!. The scallop and asparagus dish was perfection. Buttery seasoned deliciousness. Asparagus was cooked perfectly crisp. The filet mignon mushroom and asparagus dish with garlic butter mash was melt in your mouth phenomenal. Portion sizes were just right. The chocolate mousse (served inside a decadent dark chocolate cup) and  raspberry cheesecake dessert options were winners and paired very nicely with the strong cocktails. Strawberry mojito was a great starter and had a little too much fresh mint but over all was like a soda. The white cranberry Cosmo was a show stopper for me. Although my first and second were different colors ...they were equally as strong and delish. I give this place a strong 5... My best rating for a restaurant because the food was AMAZING.🍲❤ Also the service was great..they all worked quite efficiently...my food was piping hot..my glass 🍹stayed full ..and staff was quick to respond to any question I had or request. This place has regular live entertainment🎶. Lastly...The bathroom was clean and neat.🌺 I actually can't wait to return for a comedy show this weekend. Kudos Cellar Door! You have wowed this little reviewin' lady.😘 #Cheers!🍹
